summary: Kirk Cousins defied expectations by leading the Atlanta Falcons to a stunning comeback victory over the Philadelphia Eagles. Despite ongoing doubts about his abilities, Cousins orchestrated a last-minute, 70-yard drive that culminated in a game-winning touchdown pass to Bryan Edwards. This triumph has instilled confidence in the Falcons' team and their belief in Cousins as their franchise quarterback. NFL analysts and pundits alike have praised Cousins' performance, highlighting his determination and composure under pressure. The Falcons' success against the Eagles has rejuvenated their season and positioned them for a potential playoff berth.

summary: Justin Fields has emerged as a consistent performer, leading the Steelers to three consecutive wins. His growth and simplicity on the field have impressed analysts and head coaches. This decision is supported by former Steelers quarterback Ben Roethlisberger and corroborated by the team's preparation to start Fields once again. Fields has also expressed confidence in Caleb Williams, a struggling rookie quarterback, believing that he will overcome his early challenges. The Steelers are optimistic about Fields' abilities, emphasizing his growth and positive impact on the team's performance.
